<h1>画</h1><p class=neha><span style="color:#000099;">huà</span><span class=alesi>(hua4)</span> <span class=lesi>// pronunciation of 画 in Mandarin Pinyin</span></p><h2>Basic information about 画</h2><div class=abo>
<p><b>Unihan definition:</b> <a href="/dictionary/a" style="color:black;">a</a> <a href="/dictionary/painting" style="color:black;">painting</a>, <a href="/dictionary/picture" style="color:black;">picture</a>, drawing; to draw</p><p><b>Number of strokes:</b> 8<br><small>Examples of other characters consisting of 8 strokes: <a href="/character/的" title="de: possessive, adjectival suffix">的</a>, <a href="/character/和" title="he2: harmony, peace; peaceful, calm">和</a>, <a href="/character/国" title="guo2: nation, country, nation-state">国</a>, <a href="/character/到" title="dao4: go to, arrive, been to">到</a>, <a href="/character/所" title="suo3: place, location; numerary adjunct">所</a>, <a href="/character/事" title="shi4: affair, matter, business; to serve; accident, incident">事</a>, <a href="/character/经" title="jing1: classic works; pass through">经</a>, <a href="/character/法" title="fa3: law, rule, regulation, statute; France, French">法</a>, <a href="/character/学" title="xue2: learning, knowledge; school">学</a>, <a href="/character/现" title="xian4: appear, manifest, become visible">现</a></small></p><p><b>Radical:</b> <a href="/character/田" title="Kangxi radical 102">田</a>&nbsp;102.3</p><p><b>HSK level:</b> 3 <br><small>Other HSK 3 characters: <a href="/character/耳" title="er3: ear; merely, only; handle">耳</a>, <a href="/character/短" title="duan3: short; brief; deficient, lacking">短</a>, <a href="/character/楼" title="lou2: building of two or more stories">楼</a>, <a href="/character/遇" title="yu4: meet, come across, encounter">遇</a>, <a href="/character/康" title="kang1: peaceful, quiet; happy, healthy">康</a>, <a href="/character/楚" title="chu3: name of feudal state; clear">楚</a>, <a href="/character/旧" title="jiu4: old, ancient; former, past">旧</a>, <a href="/character/春" title="chun1: spring; wanton">春</a>, <a href="/character/附" title="fu4: adhere to, append; rely on near to">附</a>, <a href="/character/礼" title="li3: social custom; manners; courtesy">礼</a> <a href="/cha